The paper deals with low-rank matrix completion, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach is based on algebraic geometry and matroid theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI). The paper also presents algorithms and methods for completing and estimating errors, which are related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
